==English==

===Etymology===
Named from [[w:Donnybrook, Dublin|Donnybrook]], a suburb of Dublin, the site of a notoriously disorderly annual fair.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈdɒnɪbrʊk/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|donnybrook|donnybrooks}}

# A [[brawl]] or [[fracas]]; a scene of [[chaos]].
#:*'''2003''': The regulars here, includin' me, put up a real '''donnybrook''' to save the place. — Robert Casemore, ''Gold Is Where You Find It'' (Xlibris 2003, p. 47)